      "side": 1,
      "message": "If a SYN packet is received for a session that was previously in TIME_WAIT state, we assume we have a new session re-using the same 5-tuple.\n\nI think in this case we should also reset session-specific information in SFDP, such as bi-directional packet and bytes counts associated with the session\n\ni.e. similarly to sfdp_create_session_inline:\n\n```\n  /* Bidirectional counter zeroing */\n  vlib_zero_combined_counter (\u0026sfdp-\u003eper_session_ctr[SFDP_FLOW_COUNTER_LOOKUP],\n\t\t\t      lookup_val[0]);\n  vlib_zero_combined_counter (\u0026sfdp-\u003eper_session_ctr[SFDP_FLOW_COUNTER_LOOKUP],\n\t\t\t      lookup_val[0] | 0x1);\n  vlib_increment_simple_counter (\n    \u0026sfdp-\u003etenant_session_ctr[SFDP_TENANT_SESSION_COUNTER_CREATED],\n    thread_index, tenant_idx, 1);\n```",
      "revId": "d557b77cccaeb86874074e3aac37a11c8a6a996a",
      "serverId": "6d2eb258-4fe2-443e-8a38-ca81da23d4c2"
    },
    {
