      "writtenOn": "2026-03-12T10:23:59Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "If we reach SFDP\u0027s session count limit with a large number of sessions in TIME_WAIT state, then default behavior will be to drop new sessions (i.e on new 5-tuples) since SFDP has no capacity for additional sessions.\n\nMy assumption is that we are fine with this behavior ?",
      "revId": "d557b77cccaeb86874074e3aac37a11c8a6a996a",
      "serverId": "6d2eb258-4fe2-443e-8a38-ca81da23d4c2"
    },
    {
